                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–1049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="7" xml:id="d128fn7">Repeated to the Special Assistant at Vatican City
                        (Gowen) in Department telegram No. 18, October 11.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-10T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 10, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 10—3:39 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4232. American Catholic Bishop Walsh told officer ConGen he has been informed by
                    Papal Nuncio Riberi, Nanking, that latter has recommended immediate recognition
                    Communist regime by Vatican as only hope for maintenance Church in China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
